item.description:
My friend V introduced me to an awesome tool called PDSH. One thing that really bothered me was when logging in to machines that had a message of the day, my screen would be flooded with messages, burying the information I needed.
Here&rsquo;s how to disable MotD from appearing in the output of PDSH. In your ~/.bashrc include:
export PDSH_SSH_ARGS_APPEND=&quot;-oLogLevel=Error&quot;
